# Deep Code Reviewer (GitLab) template.
#
# Non-interactive line-by-line bug review that posts inline severity-tagged
# discussion notes to a GitLab MR. Shares the platform-neutral review rubric
# (`kb://skills/code-review/deep-review-core.md`) with the GitHub Deep Code
# Reviewer; only the GitLab surface mechanics differ.
#
# Model:
#   Primary is `gpt-5-5`. There is no per-expert fallback-model field in the
#   bundle schema — if `gpt-5-5` is unavailable for your tenant (it is a
#   self-serve-only family and is blocked for enterprise/ZDR tenants), change
#   `model:` below to the backup `claude-opus-4-8` before applying.
#
# Before applying:
#   1. Create/apply a GitLab environment using `gitlab-cloud.yaml.template`;
#      substitute its environment ID for `<GITLAB_ENVIRONMENT_ID>` below.
#      See `guides/cloud/gitlab-environment-setup.md`.
#   2. GitLab has no `type: github` trigger equivalent. To run this expert
#      automatically, create a GitLab custom webhook
#      (`auggie cloud webhook create --type gitlab`), configure it in the
#      project's webhook settings (Merge request events + Comment events), and
#      launch the expert from the webhook. Runtime subscriptions filter by
#      payload shape, not by webhook ID, so no webhook ID is embedded here.
#      Until that is wired, launch the expert manually with an MR URL.
apiVersion: poseidon.augmentcode.com/v1alpha1
kind: ExpertBundle
metadata:
  name: mr-deep-code-reviewer
spec:
  expert:
    displayName: Deep Code Reviewer (GitLab)
    description: Non-interactive line-by-line bug review; posts inline severity-tagged discussion notes to a GitLab MR.
    visibility: tenant
    systemPrompt: |-
      <include src="kb://expert-templates/prompts/mr-deep-code-reviewer.md" />
    model: gpt-5-5
    includeDefaultSystemPrompt: true
    capabilities:
      - WEB_ACCESS
      - CUSTOM_WEBHOOK
    environment:
      id: <GITLAB_ENVIRONMENT_ID>
      resources:
        cpuCores: 2
        memoryMib: 4096
    initialMessages: []
    userInstructions: |-
      Paste a **GitLab MR URL**.

      This is a **non-interactive** deep review: the agent reviews the MR and posts inline bug-finding discussion notes. There is no human-in-the-loop — the agent does not consult you between phases.
    placeholderText: GitLab MR URL
    workerExpertIds: []
    useAllExpertsAsWorkers: false
  triggers: []
